Source: National Bank of Kazakhstan, Almaty.

Comment on 2009-02-13: On 5 February 2009, the tenge was devalued. We recorded the following exchange rates: 4 February 2009 USD 1 = KZT 122.32  5 February 2009 USD 1 = KZT 143.98. Calculated devaluation: 15.0%.

Comment on 2014-02-14: On 11 February 2014, the prevailing exchange rate band was changed from 145 - 155 tenge to 182 - 188 tenge per US dollar. We recorded the following exchange rates: 11 February 2014 USD 1 = KZT 155.56 12 February 2014 USD 1 = KZT 163.90 13 February 2014 USD 1 = KZT 184.50. Calculated using the exchange rates from 11 and 13 February 2014, the tenge was devalued by 15.7%.
